race.description: New England Shade Sails Country Boosted Hcp
race.comment: YACHT GIRL (14) was only fair when resuming at Quirindi off a long break but should take plenty of improvement from that run. Gets in light at the weights and sharp improvement is anticipated. UNSOLVED (10) took a big step forward at Warren, launching late to break his maiden. The added 200m looks ideal and he shapes as a major player again. DREYMON (4) impressed two back at Beaumont but wasn't as effective at Muswellbrook, though beaten only 2.25 lengths. Likely to get back from the draw but has the turn of foot to be dangerous if the tempo is genuine. OENOLOGY (1) disappointed last time in tougher company but his run two back was full of merit when favourite. From the low draw he could find himself in a tricky spot, yet remains a safe inclusion. PUZZLE DESIGNER (2) was below his best last start but is capable of bouncing back. Keep safe.
